Palp (
Figs. 13-14
): Tibia with triangular apophysis; median apophysis hooked; embolus S-shaped, basal part relatively wide, terminal part linear.

Epigyne (
Fig. 15
): Poorly chitinised, with two parallel sutures, between them two anchoring holes.

Vulva (
Fig. 16
): Copulation ducts wide, U-shaped; spermathecae oval, wider than the ducts.
